&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-7020&quot; title=&quot;Fix release targets to account for modularization changes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-7020&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-7020&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Make the release machinery pick up the current min.version value so that the generated user docs will report the correct minimum JDK version; commit derby-7020-02-aa-fixMinJDKVersionInDocs.diff.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16702608" author="rhillegas" created="Thu, 29 Nov 2018 01:51:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving because I don&apos;t know of any more work to do on this issue. Of course, more patches may be applied if we discover other loose ends.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
